| Tier | Price | Deliverable |
|---|---|---|
| **Entry** | 4,900 THB one-time | LINE Audit + AI auto-reply + Google Sheet lead capture (3 days) |
| **Core Setup** | 15,000 THB one-time | Full system install + train + go-live (1–3 days) |
| **Starter** | 6,000 THB/mo | 1 channel + weekly report |
| **Growth** ⭐ | 9,500 THB/mo | Multi-channel + email + SLA alert + content |
| **Scale** | 15,000 THB/mo | Everything + advanced scoring + monthly review |

Entry credit applies to Core Setup if upgraded within 30 days.

---

## 8. When user asks for "next step"

Default sequence (don't deviate without checking):
1. Finish whatever file is in-progress
2. Verify (`pnpm test` + `pnpm lint` + smoke test)
3. Commit + push only when user explicitly says so
4. Suggest next file from the open todo list

Don't proactively start the next file. Ask first.

---

## 9. Hard rules (do not violate)

- Don't push to `main` without explicit "push" instruction
- Don't run destructive git commands (`reset --hard`, `force push`, `branch -D`)
- Don't commit `.env` or any `*.env.local`
- Don't add `--no-verify` to git commands
- Don't install new packages without asking (pnpm install is slow on this machine)
- Don't refactor the Command Center (`app/dashboard/command-center/*`) — internal tool, low priority
- Don't touch `proxy.ts` rate-limit logic — it's tuned and works
